data.description: Welcome to 890 Chestnut Tree Dr. in Cape St. Claire—an exceptional home boasting a unique Victorian style not typically found in this sought-after neighborhood. This remarkable home, originally built in 1983 and now available through an estate sale by its original owners, offers a distinctive layout and impressive features.  As you step onto the charming wrap-around front porch, you're greeted by the timeless elegance of this Victorian gem. This isn't a regular split-foyer that is the majority of the home style found in the neighborhood! Inside, the home features 3+ generously sized bedrooms and a unique layout including 3 3/4 baths, with one potentially serving as a convenient mudroom or doggy bath—a delightful touch for pet owners.  The master suite includes a spacious walk-in closet and full bathroom.   Additionally, the finished basement with a separate entrance provides versatile space—a potential short-stay vacation rental for added income, an ideal in-law suite, or a fantastic spot for hosting weekend football watch parties. THE CONNECTING STAIRS FROM THE KITCHEN CAN BE INSTALLED FOR APPROXIMATELY $3000  Beyond the home's exceptional features, the large yard provides ample space for outdoor enjoyment and relaxation. The garage adds convenience and utility to this already impressive property.  Located in the desirable and sought-after community of Cape St. Claire, residents enjoy a wealth of amenities, including three boat ramps for easy water access, two expansive beaches perfect for sunny days, and a welcoming community clubhouse. Moreover, the neighborhood is part of one of Anne Arundel County's top school districts, ensuring an exceptional educational experience for families.  "The Cape" offers a small-town atmosphere with local amenities such as a hardware store, grocery store, restaurants, and boutique shops, all while being conveniently situated near downtown Annapolis, Sandy Point State Park, and commuter routes to Baltimore and Washington, D.C.  Don't miss this opportunity to own a piece of Victorian charm in Cape St. Claire—schedule your showing today and envision the possibilities of making this captivating property your own. A unique blend of history, community, and convenience awaits on Chestnut Tree!
